name: Go Go Go
tag_list: online-shipping, shipping, logistics, courier-services, international-e-commerce, mail-forwarding-services
overview: Go Go Go is a company specializing in shipping, logistics, and courier services in Miami, Florida, originally founded by Juan Pablo Possenti. The organization began by offering basic packing, shipping and drop off services to a local market that focused on personal customer interaction at a retail location. The company has since expanded with a mission to provide a full range of personalized services that strategically meet the shipping needs and requirements of clientele throughout the world. Go Go Go has successfully developed a large selection of premier shipping, logistics, and courier solutions primarily for businesses that are accessed and managed through an online platform. Some of their current services include shipping rate comparison, private mailboxes, mail forwarding, and courier selection. Their customer base is now global and they cater to the needs of a variety of national and international customers. Go Go Go is also working on developing Web-based networking platforms that introduce customers to couriers and enable them to negotiate beneficial agreements. This includes allowing customers to name their shipping price based on current industry rates and receive bids from couriers within the network. As a company attuned to industry changes and client demands, Go Go Go is always adapting and changing to provide new services and products as a leader in its field. Staying aware of the latest technology in the industry, the company boasts of offering the finest in state-of-the-art technology in order to streamline customer services and provide the highest quality solutions with access to some of the best guarantees available anywhere. In addition, their logistical expertise rivals that of the largest companies in the world. Go Go Go also has a proven background in exemplary customer service with value and reliability that their clients can count on.
